result.execSummary:
The defendant Lee Carl Pitts was found guilty of the following charge(s) in this case.

  • Possess w/ Intent-THC(>200-1000g), a class H felony, Wisconsin Statutes 961.41(1m)(h)2.
  • Vehicle Operator Flee/Elude Officer, a class I felony, Wisconsin Statutes 346.04(3).

Notice to employers: It may be a violation of state law to discriminate against a job applicant because of an arrest or conviction record. Generally speaking, an employer may refuse to hire an applicant on the basis of a conviction only if the circumstances of the conviction substantially relate to the particular job. For more information, see Wisconsin Statute 111.335 and the Department of Workforce Development's publication, Arrest and Conviction Records under the Law.

records.addlTxt:
Defendant Lee Carl Pitts in court, in custody.  Attorney William Anthony Rakestraw Ii in court for Lee Carl Pitts.  Attorney Jon R Josephsen Jr. in court for State of Wisconsin. 

Sentencing proceeded. State has complied with victim notification. Statements by parties and defendant. 

AS TO COUNT 1 : The court sentenced the defendant to a MAXIMUM term in the Wisconsin State Prison of 36 MONTHS, consecutive to any other sentence; the term of INITIAL CONFINEMENT is 12 MONTHS, the term of EXTENDED SUPERVISION is 24 MONTHS.

AS TO COUNT 2 :  The court sentenced the defendant to a MAXIMUM term in the Wisconsin State Prison of 36 MONTHS, concurrent to Count 1; the term of INITIAL CONFINEMENT is 12 MONTHS, the term of EXTENDED SUPERVISION is 24 MONTHS.
 
CONDITIONS OF EXTENDED SUPERVISION:
- Absolute sobriety.
- AODA assessment, comply with recommended treatment.
- No possession, use, sale, or distribution of any illegal drugs; no association with any location where illegal substances are consumed, packaged or sold.
- Undergo random urine screens (no right to refuse screens, refusal will be treated as a positive test result) and HOC time could result from a positive test.
- DNA sample and surcharge (unless previously done).
- Pay all applicable fees of supervision.
- No possession of any firearms or ammunition.
- Maintain or seek verifiable full time employment or education or vocational training.
- Comply with all rules of extended supervision and any other conditions deemed appropriate by your agent or the court.
- Cooperate with agent.
- No operation of a motor vehicle without valid driver's license.
- Court waives all mandatory costs due to inability to pay.
- Restitution set at $0.00.

*Court finds defendant is NOT eligible for the Challenge Incarceration Program OR the Wisconsin Substance Abuse Program.
*Court advised defendant of right to seek post conviction relief.
*Court advised due to felony conviction the defendant is prohibited from firearm possession, ammunition, and defendant's voting rights are suspended and may not vote until civil rights are restored.
Defense Notice of Right to Pursue Postconviction Relief, filed.

Defendant Lee Carl Pitts in court with attorney William Anthony Rakestraw.  Defendant Lee Carl Pitts in custody, produced.  Jon R Josephsen appeared for the State of Wisconsin.

Case scheduled for Final Pretrial Conference.  Plea forms have been filed.   Parties have reached an agreement. State places offer on the record. Defense and defendant are in agreement.

As to Count 1 : Defendant changes plea(s) to GUILTY. Defendant examined as to plea, advised of Constitutional Rights and the maximum penalties. Defendant further advised that if not a US citizen, deportation is possible. Court found that the defendant knowingly, voluntarily and intelligently waived rights.  Plea Questionnaire/Waiver of Rights form, Addendum, and Elements/Jury Instructions received and filed. Parties stipulate to the Criminal Complaint as a factual basis to sustain defendant's plea(s).  Court found defendant GUILTY and ordered a Judgment of Conviction be entered on the record.  

As to Count 2 : Defendant changes plea(s) to GUILTY. Defendant examined as to plea, advised of Constitutional Rights and the maximum penalties. Defendant further advised that if not a US citizen, deportation is possible. Court found that the defendant knowingly, voluntarily and intelligently waived rights.  Plea Questionnaire/Waiver of Rights form, Addendum, and Elements/Jury Instructions received and filed. Parties stipulate to the Criminal Complaint as a factual basis to sustain defendant's plea(s).  Court found defendant GUILTY and ordered a Judgment of Conviction be entered on the record.  

*Court advised due to felony conviction the defendant is prohibited from firearm possession, body armor, and defendant's voting rights are suspended and may not vote until civil rights are restored.

The Court VACATES the Jury Trial set for 8/22/2022. Defendant remanded into custody and shall be produced for next hearing.

Case adjourned to Branch 9 for Sentencing.  Sentencing hearing scheduled for September 15, 2022 at 02:00 pm.
